#compdef bramble
# ============================================================================
# bramble - Federated GraphQL API gateway (Go, MIT)
#
# Author : Movio (movio)
# Upstream: https://github.com/movio/bramble
#
# bramble is a federated GraphQL API gateway that stitches multiple
# downstream GraphQL services into a single unified schema, in the
# style of Apollo Federation. It periodically polls each upstream
# service for its schema, computes a federation plan, and routes
# incoming GraphQL operations to the relevant upstream subset with
# parallel fan-out + result composition. Plugin hooks expose pre /
# post operation interception (rate limiting, auth, audit, response
# shaping). Operates two listeners: a public gateway endpoint and a
# private management API, both alongside a Prometheus metrics
# endpoint.
#
# The GraphQL lane is built on `github.com/99designs/gqlgen v0.17.73`
# (declared verbatim at upstream go.mod HEAD), the canonical Go
# GraphQL toolkit by 99designs (now Vista Group / vista.com,
# github.com/99designs/gqlgen, 10000+ stars). gqlgen is schema-first
# - the user writes a GraphQL SDL schema, then runs `gqlgen generate`
# to produce typed Go resolver interfaces, and implements the
# resolver methods against business logic. Bramble uses gqlgen at
# runtime to introspect downstream schemas, validate incoming
# documents, and dispatch resolvers across the federation.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 206 :: GRAPHQL (SPEC: WORKING DRAFT - OCT 2021)
# Round 1317 :: Go slot 2 of 4 :: continues Axis 206
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : async-graphql/async-graphql       [R1316 _music-player]
#   Go      : 99designs/gqlgen                  [R1317 THIS FILE]
#   TS/Node : graphql/graphql-js                [R1318 closing]
#
# All three converge on the same GraphQL spec (Facebook/Meta,
# initial release 2015, current working draft Oct 2021), but
# diverge on schema authorship workflow: async-graphql is
# code-first (derive schema from Rust types), gqlgen is
# schema-first (write SDL, generate Go interfaces), graphql-js is
# code-first (build the schema from a JS object graph). The
# gqlgen schema-first design fits the Go ecosystem's preference
# for code generation over runtime reflection.
#
# bramble is a federation gateway, which is the load-bearing
# downstream of any production GraphQL deployment past a single
# service - it lifts the "GraphQL stitching" responsibility out
# of each microservice and into a dedicated gateway tier. Apollo
# Federation v2 is the de-facto spec; bramble's pre-Apollo
# federation design is also still in production at Movio (NZ
# cinema-data SaaS) which is where the library was extracted.
# ============================================================================

_bramble() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '*-config[config file (may appear multiple times)]:file:_files -g "*.(json|yaml|yml)"' \
        '*-conf[deprecated alias for -config]:file:_files -g "*.(json|yaml|yml)"' \
        '-loglevel[log level]:level:(debug info warn error)' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]'
}

_bramble "$@"
